The assets directory is to be defined as a directory located in the project root with a file name of "assets".

The libraries directory is to be defined as a directory located in the project root with a file name of "lib"

All files in the libraries directory are distributed with a specific license to run
or link against without modification unless previously noted in the libraries directory
or otherwise noted inside of the specific library package.

All files consisting wholly or partially of plain text, intended to be 
human readable in text form and not located under the "assets" directory 
are to be considered "code", with the exception of the libraries directory.
In addition, all files located under the directory named "src" in the project
root are also to be considered code.

Unless otherwise noted all files not previously exempted are to be considered
licensed under the terms of the MIT license.

